## Ambiguity handling

Stop and report instead of guessing when:

- multiple component sets match one component name
- no stable canonical component-set node exists
- variant properties conflict with current CSS attributes
- Figma has hardcoded values where tokens are expected
- node traversal is incomplete
- token bindings are unavailable and values cannot be mapped

## Do not

- Do not derive props from screenshots alone.
- Do not derive state matrices from screenshots alone.
- Do not write `uds/components/<id>/spec.json` until node tree + variant matrix +
  doc-site comparison are complete.
- Do not invent component anatomy when layer names or nested instances are
  ambiguous.
- Do not overwrite a non-null `figmaNodeId` without reporting old/new.
- Do not omit the `Doc-site surplus` or `Snapshot delta` sections from the
  report. An inspection without them is incomplete and silently hides
  deletions and renames. If a section has no findings, say so explicitly
  (`No surplus findings.` / `Prior snapshot present: no.`) — never leave
  it blank or implicit.
